Unlike other Geevan cities these buildings do not attempt to blend in with the environment and instead sticks out entirely shining in silver coating lined with black strips along the edges. planet Koudaenao
	landscape land/desert5
	description "The planet's surface seems designed to drink up the sun, with vast stretches of land given over to alternating arrays of domed greenhouses and solar collection arrays, the better to feed towns and factories hungry not just for produce, but energy as well. In fact, evidence of any agriculture done outside of the ever-present greenhouses seems to be lacking entirely."
	spaceport "Large sections of the spaceport are given over to mass storage. Even as you watch a large shipment of food is unloaded from a ship on a neighboring pad and decanted into a nearby silo. Fresh cargo is then returned to the ship for transport offworld, but it's significantly lesser in volume that what was brought in on the same ship."

	attributes "fratmav station" uninhabited
	landscape "land/station uilenxi"
	description "A massive derelict station of unknown origin heavily damaged from time, maintained by a few rarely sighted repair bots climbing along the walls. It appears to have multiple types of ports and bays to accomodate various ships of entirely different design possibly a home to inter-specie alliance, this is also reinforced by the fact that multiple equipment and consoles found inside often comes in various shape and size while seemingly all of the same function. Many of the systems within the station appears to be active with electricity still powering the lights in many area. Thankfully the defense turrets are all broken or inactive so you're free to approach it."
	spaceport "None of the various ports on the station is compatible with your ship so you landed inside one of the open bay. From inside you can spot a few broken ships left behind varying in size from fighter to massive freighter, from quick inspection all of them are too heavily damaged to be repaired for now but if you look around carefully maybe you can find something useful."

	security 0

planet Ku'mol'akki
	attributes mining
	landscape land/badlands10
	description "This moon have only one settlement in the form of a single huge building that could easily host a town within itself with multiple large gate for land vehicles and several large bays for ships. Large Kumakk mining vehicles scour the rest of the surface occasionally returning to the settlement only for repair and maintenace."
	spaceport "Each landing area and bay have their own cranes for loading cargo into freighters. Though many seems to be empty all the time you can constantly see freighters delivering vehicle parts every hour."
	outfitter "Kumakk Basic"

planet Alkonluk
	landscape land/water12
	description "An Earth-like planet filled with mostly plants and very few small animals. Home to several Kumakk research stations."
	spaceport "There's one fairly large spaceport on top of a table-top mesa in the middle of a jungle. A few smaller buildings surround the spaceport forming a small town on top of the mesa."

planet "Zlusc Arth"
	attributes refinery station
	landscape "land/zorcn orbitalshipyard landscape"
	description "This is a massive Zorcn station that act as both fuel refinery and orbital shipyard. Designed to be capable of constructing over 300 ships in parallel it is by far the largest shipyard in this space and accounts for almost a third of ship production within the Zorcn space. Fuelled by built-in ore processing plants to directy convert materials mined from nearby asteroid belt into supplies for constructing the ships and outfits that goes inside them."
	spaceport "There are several hangar around the station all with dedicated mineral unloading area for asteroid miners to quickly and efficiently unloaded the materials, refuel, and go back to mining all in a short amount of time. There's also a decent amount of food and service facilites for workers and crews alike."
	shipyard "Zorcn Advanced"
	shipyard "Zorcn Basic"
	shipyard "Zorcn Military"
	shipyard "Zorcn Neyton"
	outfitter "Neyton Outfits"
	outfitter "Zorcn Advanced"
	outfitter "Zorcn Basic"

planet Liinoolu
	landscape "land/gw barrenB47"
	description "For most part there's nothing special about this planet other than its unusal landscape and decent mineral reserve near the surface until patches of giant mushrooms are discovered. Though few, each patch are massive and could easily span across a few kilometers."

planet Mao'luuno
	landscape "land/gw barrenA20"
	description "A small rocky planet with very hard surface almost like it was made from solid granite yet giant mushrooms can still be found, though in smaller number through the few cracks on the surface."

planet Ciuu'liion
	landscape "land/gw mountainsnowA05"
	description "Cold, rocky and unforgiving planet that on some area its cold enough to condense nitrogen into lake of liquid nitrogen and still cold enough to be uninhabitable for most living things in nearly other area. By pure chance budding of giant mushrooms can be spotting in some warmer area(which is barely a few degree celcius warmer) exposed from the ice and snow that covers most of the planet's surface."

planet Kiinoluu
	landscape "land/gw barrenB20"
	description "A rocky planet covered in large patches of moss-like vegetation, or at least in appearance. Mixed between that is patches of giant mushrooms dotted across the rocks and moss alike."

planet Tiuoon'lra
	landscape "land/gw barrenB30"
